## Statistical and Sociological Insights

Public opinion on abortion is influenced by various social factors, including religiosity, education, political views, and geographic region. For example, higher education levels and liberal political views correlate with greater support for legal abortion, while religiosity and conservative views correlate with opposition ([Open.lib.umn.edu, n.d.](https://open.lib.umn.edu/socialproblems/chapter/9-3-abortion/)).

Despite the Catholic Church's strong opposition to abortion, Catholics are not uniformly opposed, indicating the complexity of individual beliefs within religious groups ([Open.lib.umn.edu, n.d.](https://open.lib.umn.edu/socialproblems/chapter/9-3-abortion/)).

